The analyst also believes that II-VI (IIVI), led by Chief Executive Officer Vincent Mattera, is likely to benefit from AR/VR devices, with the company estimated to have roughly 25% of the 3D sensing market, down from 30% in June.

&quot;We have yet to quantify prospects from new AR/VR device opportunities, but we suspect this factors into recent stock appreciation,&quot; Leopold wrote. &quot;Apple ($AAPL) may launch a device later in 2022, but we have more work to do on this topic. We remain optimistic regarding auto applications, which have begun, but may not make meaningful contribution for several years.&quot;

II-VI (IIVI) has multiple catalysts, including the Coherent ($COHR) acquisition, which is still awaiting approval from China, but it&#39;s the company&#39;s opportunity in Silicon Carbide that management has been most positive about, Leopold added.
